CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, March 5, 1955, pg. 21, reads: "Farrell Stalwarts - Two of the key figures in Farrell High School's drive for its second state high school cage championship are pictured above with their coach, Eddie McCluskey. On the left is Charley Kemp, and on the right is Jim McCoy. Both were regulars last season. McCoy was an all-state selection. - Harris Photo"
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of Farrell High School basketball team with twelve men, including coach Eddie McCluskey, and eleven young men wearing light colored basketball uniforms, including Jim McCoy number 14, and Charley Kemp number 17 holding towel in hands, seated on bench in locker room with chalkboard in background and poster that reads "Ked's Bulletin"
